The paper discusses the use of Software-Defined Networking (SDN) and Network Function Virtualization (NFV) in Cloud computing environments, which are primarily related to computer networks (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses autonomic and timely VNF composition, deployment, and management, which are related to systems and control (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses cost and SLA-aware resource provisioning and scheduling, which are related to computer architecture (cs.CC).
